cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses access control and insider threats, which are security-related topics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a new access control model and discusses its implementation requirements. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of the proposed model on application development. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a new way of storing access authorizations as a tensor. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses how the proposed model affects command execution in applications.
